    "code": "012", 
    "data": "بِسْمِ ٱللَّهِ ٱلرَّحْمَٰنِ ٱلرَّحِيمِ\nIn the name of Allah, the Beneficent, the Merciful.\nٱقْتَرَبَتِ ٱلسَّاعَةُ وَٱنشَقَّ ٱلْقَمَرُ (1) \nThe hour drew nigh and the moon did rend asunder.\nوَإِن يَرَوْا۟ ءَايَةً يُعْرِضُوا۟ وَيَقُولُوا۟ سِحْرٌ مُّسْتَمِرٌّ (2) \nAnd if they see a miracle they turn aside and say: Transient magic.\nوَكَذَّبُوا۟ وَٱتَّبَعُوٓا۟ أَهْوَآءَهُمْ وَكُلُّ أَمْرٍ مُّسْتَقِرٌّ (3) \nAnd they call (it) a lie, and follow their low desires; and every affair has its appointed term.\nوَلَقَدْ جَآءَهُم مِّنَ ٱلْأَنۢبَآءِ مَا فِيهِ مُزْدَجَرٌ (4) \nAnd certainly some narratives have come to them wherein is prevention--\nحِكْمَةٌۢ بَٰلِغَةٌ فَمَا تُغْنِ ٱلنُّذُرُ (5) \nConsummate wisdom-- but warnings do not avail;\nفَتَوَلَّ عَنْهُمْ يَوْمَ يَدْعُ ٱلدَّاعِ إِلَىٰ شَىْءٍ نُّكُرٍ (6) \nSo turn (your) back on them (for) the day when the inviter shall invite them to a hard task,\nخُشَّعًا أَبْصَٰرُهُمْ يَخْرُجُونَ مِنَ ٱلْأَجْدَاثِ كَأَنَّهُمْ جَرَادٌ مُّنتَشِرٌ (7) \nTheir eyes cast down, going forth from their graves as if they were scattered locusts,\nمُّهْطِعِينَ إِلَى ٱلدَّاعِ يَقُولُ ٱلْكَٰفِرُونَ هَٰذَا يَوْمٌ عَسِرٌ (8) \nHastening to the inviter. The unbelievers shall say: This is a hard day.\nكَذَّبَتْ قَبْلَهُمْ قَوْمُ نُوحٍ فَكَذَّبُوا۟ عَبْدَنَا وَقَالُوا۟ مَجْنُونٌ وَٱزْدُجِرَ (9) \nBefore them the people of Nuh rejected, so they rejected Our servant and called (him) mad, and he was driven away.\nفَدَعَا رَبَّهُۥٓ أَنِّى مَغْلُوبٌ فَٱنتَصِرْ (10) \nTherefore he called upon his Lord: I am overcome, come Thou then to help.\nفَفَتَحْنَآ أَبْوَٰبَ ٱلسَّمَآءِ بِمَآءٍ مُّنْهَمِرٍ (11) \nSo We opened the gates of the cloud with water pouring\nوَفَجَّرْنَا ٱلْأَرْضَ عُيُونًا فَٱلْتَقَى ٱلْمَآءُ عَلَىٰٓ أَمْرٍ قَدْ قُدِرَ (12) \nAnd We made water to flow forth in the land in springs, so the water gathered together according to a measure already ordained.\nوَحَمَلْنَٰهُ عَلَىٰ ذَاتِ أَلْوَٰحٍ وَدُسُرٍ (13) \nAnd We bore him on that which was made of planks and nails\nتَجْرِى بِأَعْيُنِنَا جَزَآءً لِّمَن كَانَ كُفِرَ (14) \nSailing, before Our eyes, a reward for him who was denied.\nوَلَقَد تَّرَكْنَٰهَآ ءَايَةً فَهَلْ مِن مُّدَّكِرٍ (15) \nAnd certainly We left it as a sign, but is there anyone who\nفَكَيْفَ كَانَ عَذَابِى وَنُذُرِ (16) \nHow (great) was then My punishment and My warning!\nوَلَقَدْ يَسَّرْنَا ٱلْقُرْءَانَ لِلذِّكْرِ فَهَلْ مِن مُّدَّكِرٍ (17) \nAnd certainly We have made the Quran easy for remembrance, but is there anyone who will mind?\nكَذَّبَتْ عَادٌ فَكَيْفَ كَانَ عَذَابِى وَنُذُرِ (18) \nAd treated (the truth) as a lie, so how (great) was My punishment and My warning!\nإِنَّآ أَرْسَلْنَا عَلَيْهِمْ رِيحًا صَرْصَرًا فِى يَوْمِ نَحْسٍ مُّسْتَمِرٍّ (19) \nSurely We sent on them a tornado in a day of bitter ill-luck\nتَنزِعُ ٱلنَّاسَ كَأَنَّهُمْ أَعْجَازُ نَخْلٍ مُّنقَعِرٍ (20) \nTearing men away as if they were the trunks of palm-trees torn up.\nفَكَيْفَ كَانَ عَذَابِى وَنُذُرِ (21) \nHow (great) was then My punishment and My warning!\nوَلَقَدْ يَسَّرْنَا ٱلْقُرْءَانَ لِلذِّكْرِ فَهَلْ مِن مُّدَّكِرٍ (22) \nAnd certainly We have made the Quran easy for remembrance, but is there anyone who will mind?\nكَذَّبَتْ ثَمُودُ بِٱلنُّذُرِ (23) \nSamood rejected the warning.\nفَقَالُوٓا۟ أَبَشَرًا مِّنَّا وَٰحِدًا نَّتَّبِعُهُۥٓ إِنَّآ إِذًا لَّفِى ضَلَٰلٍ وَسُعُرٍ (24) \nSo they said: What! a single mortal from among us! Shall we follow him? Most surely we shall in that case be in sure error and distress:\nأَءُلْقِىَ ٱلذِّكْرُ عَلَيْهِ مِنۢ بَيْنِنَا بَلْ هُوَ كَذَّابٌ أَشِرٌ (25) \nHas the reminder been made to light upon him from among us? Nay! he is an insolent liar!\nسَيَعْلَمُونَ غَدًا مَّنِ ٱلْكَذَّابُ ٱلْأَشِرُ (26) \nTomorrow shall they know who is the liar, the insolent one.\nإِنَّا مُرْسِلُوا۟ ٱلنَّاقَةِ فِتْنَةً لَّهُمْ فَٱرْتَقِبْهُمْ وَٱصْطَبِرْ (27) \nSurely We are going to send the she-camel as a trial for them; therefore watch them and have patience.\nوَنَبِّئْهُمْ أَنَّ ٱلْمَآءَ قِسْمَةٌۢ بَيْنَهُمْ كُلُّ شِرْبٍ مُّحْتَضَرٌ (28) \nAnd inform them that the water is shared between them; every share of the water shall be regulated.\nفَنَادَوْا۟ صَاحِبَهُمْ فَتَعَاطَىٰ فَعَقَرَ (29) \nBut they called their companion, so he took (the sword) and slew (her).\nفَكَيْفَ كَانَ عَذَابِى وَنُذُرِ (30) \nHow (great) was then My punishment and My warning!\nإِنَّآ أَرْسَلْنَا عَلَيْهِمْ صَيْحَةً وَٰحِدَةً فَكَانُوا۟ كَهَشِيمِ ٱلْمُحْتَظِرِ (31) \nSurely We sent upon them a single cry, so they were like the dry fragments of trees which the maker of an enclosure collects.\nوَلَقَدْ يَسَّرْنَا ٱلْقُرْءَانَ لِلذِّكْرِ فَهَلْ مِن مُّدَّكِرٍ (32) \nAnd certainly We have made the Quran easy for remembrance, but is there anyone who will mind?\nكَذَّبَتْ قَوْمُ لُوطٍۭ بِٱلنُّذُرِ (33) \nThe people of Lut treated the warning. as a lie.\nإِنَّآ أَرْسَلْنَا عَلَيْهِمْ حَاصِبًا إِلَّآ ءَالَ لُوطٍ نَّجَّيْنَٰهُم بِسَحَرٍ (34) \nSurely We sent upon them a stonestorm, except Lut's followers; We saved them a little before daybreak,\nنِّعْمَةً مِّنْ عِندِنَا كَذَٰلِكَ نَجْزِى مَن شَكَرَ (35) \nA favor from Us; thus do We reward him who gives thanks.\nوَلَقَدْ أَنذَرَهُم بَطْشَتَنَا فَتَمَارَوْا۟ بِٱلنُّذُرِ (36) \nAnd certainly he warned them of Our violent seizure, but they obstinately disputed the warning.\nوَلَقَدْ رَٰوَدُوهُ عَن ضَيْفِهِۦ فَطَمَسْنَآ أَعْيُنَهُمْ فَذُوقُوا۟ عَذَابِى وَنُذُرِ (37) \nAnd certainly they endeavored to turn him from his guests, but We blinded their eyes; so taste My chastisement and My warning.\nوَلَقَدْ صَبَّحَهُم بُكْرَةً عَذَابٌ مُّسْتَقِرٌّ (38) \nAnd certainly a lasting chastisement overtook them in the morning.\nفَذُوقُوا۟ عَذَابِى وَنُذُرِ (39) \nSo taste My chastisement and My warning.\nوَلَقَدْ يَسَّرْنَا ٱلْقُرْءَانَ لِلذِّكْرِ فَهَلْ مِن مُّدَّكِرٍ (40) \nAnd certainly We have made the Quran easy for remembrance, but is there anyone who will mind?\nوَلَقَدْ جَآءَ ءَالَ فِرْعَوْنَ ٱلنُّذُرُ (41) \nAnd certainly the warning came to Firon's people.\nكَذَّبُوا۟ بِـَٔايَٰتِنَا كُلِّهَا فَأَخَذْنَٰهُمْ أَخْذَ عَزِيزٍ مُّقْتَدِرٍ (42) \nThey rejected all Our communications, so We overtook them after the manner of a Mighty, Powerful One.\nأَكُفَّارُكُمْ خَيْرٌ مِّنْ أُو۟لَٰٓئِكُمْ أَمْ لَكُم بَرَآءَةٌ فِى ٱلزُّبُرِ (43) \nAre the unbelievers of yours better than these, or is there an exemption for you in the scriptures?\nأَمْ يَقُولُونَ نَحْنُ جَمِيعٌ مُّنتَصِرٌ (44) \nOr do they say: We are a host allied together to help each other?\nسَيُهْزَمُ ٱلْجَمْعُ وَيُوَلُّونَ ٱلدُّبُرَ (45) \nSoon shall the hosts be routed, and they shall turn (their) backs.\nبَلِ ٱلسَّاعَةُ مَوْعِدُهُمْ وَٱلسَّاعَةُ أَدْهَىٰ وَأَمَرُّ (46) \nNay, the hour is their promised time, and the hour shall be most grievous and bitter.\nإِنَّ ٱلْمُجْرِمِينَ فِى ضَلَٰلٍ وَسُعُرٍ (47) \nSurely the guilty are in error and distress.\nيَوْمَ يُسْحَبُونَ فِى ٱلنَّارِ عَلَىٰ وُجُوهِهِمْ ذُوقُوا۟ مَسَّ سَقَرَ (48) \nOn the day when they shall be dragged upon their faces into the fire; taste the touch of hell.\nإِنَّا كُلَّ شَىْءٍ خَلَقْنَٰهُ بِقَدَرٍ (49) \nSurely We have created everything according to a measure.\nوَمَآ أَمْرُنَآ إِلَّا وَٰحِدَةٌ كَلَمْحٍۭ بِٱلْبَصَرِ (50) \nAnd Our command is but one, as the twinkling of an eye.\nوَلَقَدْ أَهْلَكْنَآ أَشْيَاعَكُمْ فَهَلْ مِن مُّدَّكِرٍ (51) \nAnd certainly We have already destroyed the likes of you, but is there anyone who will mind?\nوَكُلُّ شَىْءٍ فَعَلُوهُ فِى ٱلزُّبُرِ (52) \nAnd everything they have done is in the writings.\nوَكُلُّ صَغِيرٍ وَكَبِيرٍ مُّسْتَطَرٌ (53) \nAnd everything small and great is written down.\nإِنَّ ٱلْمُتَّقِينَ فِى جَنَّٰتٍ وَنَهَرٍ (54) \nSurely those who guard (against evil) shall be in gardens and rivers,\nفِى مَقْعَدِ صِدْقٍ عِندَ مَلِيكٍ مُّقْتَدِرٍۭ (55) \nIn the seat of honor with a most Powerful King.", 
    "title": "54: Al-Qamar القمر"
}